<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[172,1127,1385,1579]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
The species is described from 
<collectingCountry box="[609,690,1385,1411]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">France</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="SIMON, E." box="[740,898,1385,1411]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 272" refId="ref5849" refString="SIMON, E. (1874): Les arachnides de France. - Roret, Paris, pp. 1 - 272." type="book chapter" year="1874">SIMON (1874)</bibRefCitation>
and is distributed from the Azores to the west to eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[622,710,1418,1444]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, and from 
<collectingCountry box="[834,987,1418,1444]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
to Crimean Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="ROBERTS, M. J." box="[306,467,1452,1479]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" refId="ref5634" refString="ROBERTS, M. J. (1985): The spiders of Great Britain and Ireland, Volume 1: Atypidae to Theridiosomatidae. - Harley Books, Colchester." type="book" year="1985">ROBERTS 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BORGES, P. A. V. &amp; WUNDERLICH, J." box="[477,814,1452,1478]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="249 - 282" refId="ref3791" refString="BORGES, P. A. V. &amp; WUNDERLICH, J. (2008): Spider biodiversity patterns and their conservation in the Azorean archipelago, with descriptions of new species. - Systematics and Biodiversity 6: 249 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 1477200008002648" type="journal article" year="2008">BORGES &amp; WUNDERLICH 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="DANISMAN, T. &amp; GUNDUZ, G. &amp; BAYRAM, A. &amp; COSAR, I. &amp; ALLAHVERDI, H." box="[823,1071,1452,1478]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="63 - 67" refId="ref4207" refString="DANISMAN, T., GUNDUZ, G., BAYRAM, A., COSAR, I. &amp; ALLAHVERDI, H. (2014): Contributions to the knowledge of dictynid spider fauna of Turkey (Araneae, Dictynidae). - Serket 14: 63 - 67." type="journal article" year="2014">
DANIŞMAN 
<emphasis box="[956,1001,1452,1478]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
, KOVBLYUK 
<emphasis box="[263,315,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
2016, 
<bibRefCitation author="WSC" box="[386,513,1486,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" refId="ref6032" refString="WSC (2020): World Spider Catalog. Version 20.0. Natural History Museum Bern, online at http: // wsc. nmbe. ch [accessed on 20.08.2020] https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="url" year="2020">WSC 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The closest reported localities to 
<collectingCountry box="[917,1019,1485,1511]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
are from North 
<collectingCountry box="[252,386,1519,1545]" name="Macedonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
and three Greek islands (Chios, Lesvos and Naxos) (
<bibRefCitation author="PARASCHI, L." pageId="1" pageNumber="64" refId="ref5531" refString="PARASCHI, L. (1988): Study of spiders in maquis ecosystems of southern Greece (mainland - insular). - PhD thesis, University of Athens, Department of Biology, Section of Ecology and Taxonomy, 237 pp." type="book" year="1988">PARASCHI 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BOSMANS, R. &amp; BAERT, L. &amp; BOSSELAERS, J. &amp; DE KONINCK, H. &amp; MAELFAIT, J. - P. &amp; VAN KEER, J." box="[241,471,1553,1579]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref3870" refString="BOSMANS, R., BAERT, L., BOSSELAERS, J., DE KONINCK, H., MAELFAIT, J. - P. &amp; VAN KEER, J. (2009): Spiders of Lesbos (Greece). - Nieuwsbrief van de Belgische Arachnologische Vereniging 24 (Suppl.): 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="2009">
BOSMANS 
<emphasis box="[356,401,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
, RUSSELL- 
<bibRefCitation author="SMITH, A. &amp; ALLISON, R. &amp; ASKINS, M. &amp; BLUMSOM, W. &amp; SNAZELL, R. &amp; SPILLING, C." box="[586,779,1553,1579]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="133 - 167" refId="ref5715" refString="RUSSELL- SMITH, A., ALLISON, R., ASKINS, M., BLUMSOM, W., SNAZELL, R. &amp; SPILLING, C. (2011): A provisional checklist and gazetteer of the spiders of Chios, Greece (Arachnida: Araneae). - Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 15: 133 - 167. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2010.15.5.133" type="journal article" year="2011">
SMITH 
<emphasis box="[664,709,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="NENTWIG, W. &amp; BLICK, T. &amp; BOSMANS, R. &amp; GLOOR, D. &amp; HANGGI, A. &amp; KROPF, C." box="[789,1022,1553,1579]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="2020" refId="ref5394" refString="NENTWIG, W., BLICK, T., BOSMANS, R., GLOOR, D., HANGGI, A. &amp; KROPF, C. (2020): Araneae. [Internet] Version {1}. 2020. Online at https: // www. araneae. nmbe. ch [accessed on 20.08.2020] https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 1" type="journal article" year="2020">
NENTWIG 
<emphasis box="[905,958,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
